ails-bike-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 630w\" ezoid=\"0.9695692932902349\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike-696x464.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike-1068x712.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Cand-aid-treads-and-trails-bike-630x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 630w\"></a></p><p>Can’d Aid is built on the premise of “Do Good. Feel Good.” From their Treads+Trails program to donating canned drinking water to those in need, like those without clean drinking water due to the winter storm in Texas, Can’d Aid does a lot of good for a lot of people.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021.jpg\" alt=\"Lazer Helmets &amp; Can'd Aid Gekko kids helmet\" width=\"1200\" height=\"960\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-297x238.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-800x640.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-120x96.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-768x614.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-696x557.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-1068x854.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-525x420.jpg 525w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-297x238.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-800x640.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-120x96.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-768x614.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-696x557.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-1068x854.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Lazer-Gekko-kids-helmet-buy-one-save-one-program-2021-525x420.jpg 525w\"></a></p><p>This time, in partnership with Lazer Helmets, the Buy One, Save Another program will lead to donations of the Lazer Gekko kids helmet to worthy kiddos. Right off the bat, Lazer is donating 200 Gekko helmets. On top of that, for every 10 Lazer helmets sold, they will donate one Gekko helmet.</p><p>The catch? You have to head over to their <span lang=\"NL\"><a href=\"https://lazersport.us/pages/product-registration\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://lazersport.us/pages/product-registration&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1614788715136000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFqOVliREMgUyX-DxBH3vTXv8liuA\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Product Registration</span></b></a></span><b> </b>page, and register your helmet. This will directly benefit you, however, as it will extend your helmet warranty from 12 months to 24 months.</p><p>According to Lazer, “With the Buy One, Save Another program, Lazer aims to get more kids on bikes and help protect them while they ride. Kicking off the campaign, Lazer will donate 200 helmets to get started and then every registered helmet will count toward the donation program. Lazer is excited to support Can’d Aid and its mission to build community and foster outdoor opportunities for youth. The non-profit helps promote healthy and active lifestyles by providing kids with skateboards and bikes as well as organizing volunteers to build multi-use trails.”</p><p>The program will run from March 1st to the end of May.</p><p><a href=\"https://lazersport.us/pages/bosa\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>lazersport.us</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3937f973c8fb3c3b15f5677f795ee1f21cf501f65fcec86d0767b8a130c6ed5b","category":"Cycling"}